SIMPLE: expansive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Expansive
<hw>Ex*pan"sive</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧ks*p⟦acr⟧n"s⟦icr⟧v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>expansif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a
capacity or tendency to expand or dilate; diffusive; of much expanse;
wide-extending; <as>as, the <ex>expansive</ex> force of heat; the
<ex>expansive</ex> quality of air.</as></def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A more <qex>expansive</qex> and generous compassion.</q>
<rj><qau>Eustace.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His forehead was broad and <qex>expansive</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Prescott.</qau></rj></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>causing expansion; <as>as, the <ex>expansive</ex>
force of heat</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>of much expanse; wide-extending; <as>as, an
<ex>expansive</ex> view of the mountains</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>friendly, open, and unrestrained in conversation or
discourse; -- of people; <as>as, wine made the guest
<ex>expansive</ex></as>.</def> <wns>[wns=4]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> effusive, talkative.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>characterized by exaggerated feelings of euphoria
and delusions of grandeur.</def> <wns>[wns=3]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ex*pan"sive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>
-<wf>Ex*pan"sive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>expansiveness</ent>⟦br⟧
